## 1. Project Overview

### Problem Statement
Students applying for internships/placements waste hours filling out the same personal details across dozens of career portals. Each portal has a slightly different form layout, field naming, and structure — making simple copy-paste insufficient.

### Solution
**AutoFill AI** is a Chrome extension that:
1. Lets users create a **master profile** once (name, education, skills, experience, resume, etc.)
2. **Detects** form fields on any career/job portal page
3. Uses **AI (Gemini API)** to intelligently match user profile data to form fields — even when labels are ambiguous or non-standard
4. **Auto-fills** the form in one click
5. **Asks the user** for any field it can't confidently fill (unseen/unknown questions)

### Key Differentiators
- Works on **any** career portal (not hard-coded to specific sites)
- Uses **AI-driven semantic matching** — not brittle regex/keyword matching
- Handles **dropdowns, textareas, radio buttons, checkboxes** — not just text inputs
- **Learns** from user corrections over time (optional enhancement)

