## 2. Complete Tech Stack

### Frontend (Chrome Extension)

| Technology | Purpose | Why This Choice |
|---|---|---|
| **React 18+** | Extension Popup & Options Page UI | Component-based, great DX, rich ecosystem |
| **TypeScript** | Type safety across the entire extension | Catches bugs early, better IDE support |
| **Vite** | Build tool / bundler | Blazing fast HMR, native ES modules |
| **CRXJS Vite Plugin** | Chrome Extension build integration | Reads `manifest.json`, auto-generates valid extension structure |
| **Vanilla CSS / CSS Modules** | Styling | Scoped styles, no runtime overhead in content scripts |
| **Chrome APIs** | Storage, messaging, tabs | Native extension capabilities |

### Content Script (Injected into Web Pages)

| Technology | Purpose | Why This Choice |
|---|---|---|
| **Vanilla TypeScript** | DOM scraping & form filling | React is too heavy to inject into every page; pure TS is lightweight |
| **MutationObserver API** | Detect dynamically loaded forms (SPAs) | Many career portals use React/Angular — forms load asynchronously |

### Background Script (Service Worker)

| Technology | Purpose | Why This Choice |
|---|---|---|
| **TypeScript** | Message routing, API calls, storage management | Consistent type safety with the rest of the codebase |
| **Chrome Extension Service Worker API** | Event-driven background processing | Required by Manifest V3 |

### Backend Server

