### 4.3 Data Model: FormField

```typescript
interface FormField {
  // Unique CSS selector to re-find this element
  selector: string;
  
  // Human-readable label extracted from the page
  label: string;
  
  // HTML input type
  type: 'text' | 'email' | 'tel' | 'number' | 'date' | 'select' | 
        'radio' | 'checkbox' | 'textarea' | 'file' | 'url' | 'hidden';
  
  // For select/radio/checkbox: available options
  options?: string[];
  
  // Current value (if pre-filled)
  currentValue?: string;
  
  // Whether the field is required
  required: boolean;
  
  // Contextual hints (nearby text, section heading, etc.)
  context?: string;
  
  // The placeholder text if any
  placeholder?: string;
}
```

