## 10. Security & Privacy

> [!CAUTION]
> This extension handles sensitive personal data. Security is non-negotiable.

### 10.1 Data Storage Security

| Concern | Solution |
|---|---|
| User profile stored locally | Use `chrome.storage.local` (sandboxed per extension) |
| Sensitive fields (DOB, phone) | Never send to backend unless needed for matching |
| API keys | **Never** store in frontend code. Only on the backend `.env` |
| Resume text | Strip PII before logging / analytics |

### 10.2 Communication Security

| Concern | Solution |
|---|---|
| Extension ↔ Backend | Always HTTPS in production |
| CORS | Strict `chrome-extension://YOUR_ID` origin only |
| Rate limiting | 100 req/15min per IP |
| Request validation | Sanitize & validate all inputs server-side |
| API authentication | Extension sends a unique `X-Extension-ID` header; backend validates |

### 10.3 Content Script Security

| Concern | Solution |
|---|---|
| XSS via injected values | Never inject raw HTML; only set `.value` properties |
| Selector injection | Sanitize selectors with `CSS.escape()` |
| Data leakage | Content script only reads DOM — never sends page content to third parties |

### 10.4 Privacy Policy Requirements

If publishing to Chrome Web Store:
- Declare all data usage in the extension manifest
- Create a privacy policy page
- Clearly state that data is stored locally by default
- Disclose AI API usage and what data is sent to the server

