## 11. Edge Cases & Error Handling

### Form-Related Edge Cases

| Scenario | Solution |
|---|---|
| **Multi-step forms** (wizard-style) | Detect when new fields appear via `MutationObserver`; offer to auto-fill each step |
| **Shadow DOM** (Web Components) | Use `element.shadowRoot?.querySelectorAll()` as a fallback |
| **iframes** | Content scripts don't run in cross-origin iframes by default. Add `"all_frames": true` to manifest and handle same-origin iframes |
| **CAPTCHA fields** | Detect & skip CAPTCHA elements (common class names / `data-sitekey`) |
| **File upload fields** | Cannot be programmatically filled. Highlight and notify user |
| **Dynamic dropdowns** (AJAX-loaded options) | Wait for options to load before scraping (`MutationObserver` on the `<select>`) |
| **React/Angular controlled inputs** | Use native value setters + synthetic events (already handled in `filler.ts`) |
| **Already-filled fields** | Skip fields that have existing values; offer override option |

### API Edge Cases

| Scenario | Solution |
|---|---|
| AI returns invalid JSON | Wrap in try/catch; retry once with a simplified prompt |
| AI times out | Set 30s timeout; show partial results if any |
| Backend is down | Fall back to a local keyword-based matcher (no AI) |
| Rate limit exceeded | Queue requests; show "please wait" message |
| Profile is incomplete | Warn user; fill what's available; mark non-fillable fields |

